				<h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-charcoal-900 text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Key Advantages of Preneed for Veterans</h3>
				<ul class="space-y-3 list-none pl-0">
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Locks in today's prices:</strong> The VA burial allowance is a fixed dollar amount that rarely increases. Meanwhile, funeral costs rise 3–5% per year. Preneed insurance freezes your costs at today's rates.</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Documents exact wishes:</strong> Military honors combined with personal preferences — specific hymns, readings, unit involvement, flag recipient designation — are all recorded in the preneed plan.</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Pays the funeral home directly:</strong> Your family doesn't have to front thousands of dollars and wait for VA reimbursement. The preneed policy pays the funeral home upon need, and VA benefits are received separately.</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Works alongside VA benefits:</strong> Preneed insurance supplements VA benefits — it doesn't replace them. Your family receives the full value of both.</span>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-charcoal-900 text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Example Scenario</h3>
				<p>A retired Army veteran in Fayetteville has full VA burial benefits and chooses burial at Sandhills State Veterans Cemetery. The VA covers the plot, headstone, and opening/closing. The veteran also has a preneed insurance policy that covers the funeral home services, casket, transportation, flowers, programs, and reception. When the time comes, the family's out-of-pocket cost is <strong>$0</strong>. The funeral home is paid by the preneed policy. The VA provides the cemetery benefits. The family can focus entirely on grieving, remembering, and honoring their loved one.</p>
			</div>
