		<!-- Section 7: Pre-Planning for Veterans Checklist -->
		<section class="mb-16">
			<SectionHeading title="Pre-Planning for Veterans: What to Document" accent />
			<div class="prose max-w-none text-charcoal-700 space-y-4">
				<p>Veterans who want to ensure their families are fully prepared should gather and organize the following documents and decisions. This checklist works hand-in-hand with a preneed insurance plan — together, they give your family everything they need.</p>

				<h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-charcoal-900 text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Essential Documents</h3>
				<ul class="space-y-3 list-none pl-0">
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>DD-214 (Certificate of Release or Discharge from Active Duty):</strong> This is the most important document for establishing VA burial benefit eligibility. Keep the original in a safe, accessible location and give a copy to your preneed funeral director.</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>VA benefits letter:</strong> Confirms your current VA benefit status and eligibility.</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Medal and award documentation:</strong> Specific medals or commendations you want recognized during the service or inscribed on the headstone.</span>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-charcoal-900 text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Military Service Details to Record</h3>
				<ul class="space-y-3 list-none pl-0">
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span>Branch of service (Army, Navy, Air Force, Marines, Coast Guard, Space Force)</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span>Dates of service (entry and discharge)</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span>Rank at discharge</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span>Unit assignments (especially for honor guard coordination)</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span>Wartime service periods (Korea, Vietnam, Desert Storm, OEF/OIF, etc.)</span>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-charcoal-900 text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Funeral and Memorial Preferences</h3>
				<ul class="space-y-3 list-none pl-0">
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Burial location:</strong> National cemetery, state veterans cemetery, or private cemetery</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Military honors:</strong> Standard honors (two-person detail, flag folding, Taps) or full honors (gun salute, caisson, honor guard)</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Flag recipient:</strong> Who should receive the folded flag — spouse, child, parent, or another person</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Personal elements:</strong> Specific hymns, scripture readings, poems, or songs</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Special requests:</strong> Unit involvement, buddy escort, specific veterans organization participation (VFW, American Legion)</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-charcoal-700">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-teal-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
						<span><strong>Burial vs. cremation preference:</strong> And if cremation, whether the urn will be interred, placed in a columbarium, or kept by the family</span>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<p class="mt-6">When you combine this documentation with a preneed insurance plan, every detail is accounted for — both the financial coverage and the personal wishes. Your family will have a complete roadmap. No guesswork. No scrambling. No unexpected bills. Learn more about <a href="/plan-ahead" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700 underline">how preneed planning works</a> or visit our <a href="/faq" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700 underline">FAQ page</a> for additional questions.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

